* BrightBlade shook her head again and focused on rhe cuffs on her wrists, 
but still not seeing them.
The feeling that she was a real Maximal was still growing, as well as her 
feelings for this Maximal that she would have sooner shot a minuet ago.
What in the Pit was going on?!
She was a Predacon but her mind was telling her that she was a Maximal, and 
now she felt a slight longing for a bot she had never met before now!
Something was definetly wrong! Maybe even with her.
BrightBlade closed her optics, as if anybot would love her. Maximal or 
Predacon. No bot had ever really loved her: Gangon alwasy commented on her 
looks but he never showed any signs that he loved her, Perndabot only liked 
her for her looks and not her real self.
But now there was this strong feeling that she was finally loved, the 
thought actually warming her spark a bit.
But it was brought on by the thoughts, otherwise she wouldn't give a rats 
tail about any of this.
BrightBlade looked at the cuffs again but then noticed something, Grimmler 
was apporaching her.
But why in the Hell should she feel so attracted to a slaging Maximal?
It wasn't right, but the more she fought against it the stronger it became.
She sighed again and looked at the cuffs, knowing that each step the man 
took towards her her love for him grew.
It was frustrating as Hell but she couldn't fight it, not even the fact that 
her mind told her she was a Maximal.
It was so strange.*
